<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="54" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[160,1156,1248,1689]" box="[160,276,1248,1273]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,1248,1273]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[160,1156,1248,1689]" pageId="2" pageNumber="54">
Body surface coarsely and densely punctate; body length varying from 4.0 to 
<quantity box="[1062,1152,1284,1308]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
. Mandible of female with four teeth; juxtantennal carina strong; clypeus with margin denticulate; pronotal lobe with carina; omaulus with short carina; scutoscutellar suture deeply foveate; a distinct notch between scutellum and axilla; scutellum with translucent apical lamella only laterally; propodeum with row of pits across the base and with large fovea behind spiracle; fore and mid tibiae with one spine on the outer apical margin; apex of female hind tibia with flat projection; arolia present in both sexes; T1 with a line delimiting basal concavity; distal margin of female T1 with short hairs; T6 of female truncated with a median subapical fovea; female S6 strongly curved at apex and slightly exceeding T6. Male with T7 small, rounded or weakly bilobed; the two basalmost sterna long; S3–S4 with fringes of long hairs arched toward the middle; and S5 with a small lateral tooth. Male gonostyli with about the same width across their entire length, without lateral expansions or angulations.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
